Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> query
Rule 1     query -> select_stmt
Rule 2     select_stmt -> SELECT select_list FROM ID
Rule 3     select_list -> STAR
Rule 4     select_list -> column_list
Rule 5     column_list -> ID
Rule 6     column_list -> column_list COMMA ID

Terminals, with rules where they appear

COMMA                : 6
FROM                 : 2
ID                   : 2 5 6
SELECT               : 2
STAR                 : 3
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

column_list          : 4 6
query                : 0
select_list          : 2
select_stmt          : 1

Parsing method: LALR

state 0

    (0) S' -> . query
    (1) query -> . select_stmt
    (2) select_stmt -> . SELECT select_list FROM ID

    SELECT          shift and go to state 3

    query                          shift and go to state 1
    select_stmt                    shift and go to state 2

state 1

    (0) S' -> query .



state 2

    (1) query -> select_stmt .

    $end            reduce using rule 1 (query -> select_stmt .)


state 3

    (2) select_stmt -> SELECT . select_list FROM ID
    (3) select_list -> . STAR
    (4) select_list -> . column_list
    (5) column_list -> . ID
    (6) column_list -> . column_list COMMA ID

    STAR            shift and go to state 6
    ID              shift and go to state 5

    select_list                    shift and go to state 4
    column_list                    shift and go to state 7

state 4

    (2) select_stmt -> SELECT select_list . FROM ID

    FROM            shift and go to state 8


state 5

    (5) column_list -> ID .

    COMMA           reduce using rule 5 (column_list -> ID .)
    FROM            reduce using rule 5 (column_list -> ID .)


state 6

    (3) select_list -> STAR .

    FROM            reduce using rule 3 (select_list -> STAR .)


state 7

    (4) select_list -> column_list .
    (6) column_list -> column_list . COMMA ID

    FROM            reduce using rule 4 (select_list -> column_list .)
    COMMA           shift and go to state 9


state 8

    (2) select_stmt -> SELECT select_list FROM . ID

    ID              shift and go to state 10


state 9

    (6) column_list -> column_list COMMA . ID

    ID              shift and go to state 11


state 10

    (2) select_stmt -> SELECT select_list FROM ID .

    $end            reduce using rule 2 (select_stmt -> SELECT select_list FROM ID .)


state 11

    (6) column_list -> column_list COMMA ID .

    COMMA           reduce using rule 6 (column_list -> column_list COMMA ID .)
    FROM            reduce using rule 6 (column_list -> column_list COMMA ID .)

